<li id="cite_note-68"><b><a href="#cite_ref-68" title="">^</a></b> "Bayh Calls for Nixon's Support As Senate Gets Electoral Plan", The New York Times, August 15, 1970, page 11</li>
<li id="cite_note-NYT-9-18-70-69">^ <a href="#cite_ref-NYT-9-18-70_69-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-NYT-9-18-70_69-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-NYT-9-18-70_69-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> "Senate Refuses To Halt Debate On Direct Voting," The New York Times, September 18, 1970, page 1</li>
<li id="cite_note-70"><b><a href="#cite_ref-70" title="">^</a></b> "Senate Debating Direct Election", The New York Times, September 9, 1970, page 10</li>
<li id="cite_note-71"><b><a href="#cite_ref-71" title="">^</a></b> The Senate reduced the required vote from two-thirds to three-fifths (i.e., 60 vote). <i>See</i> <a href="http://www.senate.gov/artandhistory/history/common/briefing/Filibuster_Cloture.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.senate.gov/artandhistory/history/common/briefing/Filibuster_Cloture.htm" rel="nofollow">United States Senate website.</a></li>
